
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Louvre Museum Exhibition Management System

class Location {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -description: String
}

class Exhibition {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -status: String
  -coordinator: Employee
}

class Employee {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -position: String
  -coach: Employee
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  -id: int
  -itemDescription: String
  -desiredPieces: int
}

class Piece {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -artist: String
  -collector: Collector
}

class Collector {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -contactInfo: String
}

class Request {
  -id: int
  -exhibitionItem: ExhibitionItem
  -piece: Piece
  -status: String
  -requestedBy: Employee
}

' Relationships

Location "1" --> "0..*" Exhibition : contains

Exhibition "1" --> "1" Employee : has coordinator

Employee "1" --> "0..1" Employee : is coached by

Exhibition "1" --> "0..*" ExhibitionItem : includes

ExhibitionItem "1" --> "0..*" Request : has requests

Request "1" --> "1" Piece : requests

Piece "1" --> "1" Collector : belongs to
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Classes:

- **`Location`**: Represents areas within the museum that can host exhibitions (e.g., wings, floors).
- **`Exhibition`**: A planned exhibition with start/end dates, title, status, and a coordinator.
- **`Employee`**: Museum staff, with a potential coach (senior employee).
- **`ExhibitionItem`**: An item or type of artwork desired in an exhibition.
- **`Piece`**: A specific artwork piece available from a collector.
- **`Collector`**: External entity owning pieces.
- **`Request`**: A request made by an employee for a specific piece for an exhibition item.

---

### Relationships:
- Each `Location` can contain multiple `Exhibitions`.
- Each `Exhibition` has exactly one `Employee` as its coordinator.
- Each `Employee` may have one `Employee` as their coach.
- Each `Exhibition` may include multiple `ExhibitionItems`.
- Each `ExhibitionItem` can be associated with multiple `Request`s.
- Each `Request` links a specific `Piece` to an `ExhibitionItem`.
- Each `Piece` belongs to one `Collector`.

---

